33:58.066 --> 33:59.985
Hello?

33:59.986 --> 34:01.146
Yeah.

34:02.826 --> 34:06.225
Well, no, they're going to lose
the case for a lot of reasons, Mike.

34:06.226 --> 34:09.545
Duh - I didn't do anything. Number
two, there's no murder weapon.

34:09.545 --> 34:11.185
Number three, there's no motive.

34:11.186 --> 34:13.145
Jesus!

34:13.146 --> 34:14.386
Ah, OK.

34:21.786 --> 34:24.424
Oh, you know what?
That's another one. Rosemary...

34:24.425 --> 34:27.704
You know how many times I've seen
Rosemary in my whole life? Twice.

34:27.705 --> 34:30.024
Once 15 years ago and then

34:30.025 --> 34:33.905
one time she came down for
Margaret's graduation. That was it.

34:35.105 --> 34:37.545
Yeah. Oh, yeah. He's hired, yeah.

34:38.625 --> 34:42.623
Well, as I have always cautioned,
never underestimate anybody.

34:42.625 --> 34:45.784
It's a good way to lose
football games and wars.

34:47.665 --> 34:50.264
I don't know, I just, I found myself
a couple of times, like,

34:50.264 --> 34:53.384
sitting up straighter in court when
people were talking about my dad

34:53.385 --> 34:55.623
and I'll just,
I'll be really, like, indignant,

34:55.625 --> 34:58.344
I'll just be like, "This is
my father you're talking about,

34:58.345 --> 35:01.624
"you know, like I have a lot of
pride in him, this is our family

35:01.625 --> 35:04.944
"you're talking about," and
the fact that I know he's innocent

35:04.945 --> 35:09.344
and the fact that, like, hopefully
people can see it through me now,

35:09.345 --> 35:12.825
people can see it in me
that he is innocent and...

35:15.385 --> 35:19.424
I don't know, I think, I think that
helps, sometimes, to get through it.

35:19.425 --> 35:22.424
You know the DA's trying to
say basically that our dad

35:22.425 --> 35:26.664
killed our birth mother and our
mother, but where are we sitting?

35:26.665 --> 35:28.385
We're sitting behind our dad.

35:29.825 --> 35:32.504
Now, shortly before she died,

35:32.505 --> 35:35.944
I think it was the Thursday of
the week before Thanksgiving,

35:35.945 --> 35:40.544
you talked with Liz and she talked
about suffering severe headaches.

35:40.545 --> 35:44.144
She came to my room about
three o'clock on that Thursday

35:44.145 --> 35:45.944
and she was pale.

35:45.945 --> 35:49.584
She looked bad and
she held her head like this

35:49.585 --> 35:51.304
and she said... I asked her

35:51.305 --> 35:55.024
what was wrong and she said she just
had the most severe headache

35:55.025 --> 35:59.304
and that she did make an appointment
to go to the medical facility

35:59.305 --> 36:02.864
and that she had an appointment on
Tuesday. The following week. Yes.

36:02.865 --> 36:06.224
So she never actually got to see a
doctor about these severe headaches.

36:06.225 --> 36:07.584
No.

36:07.585 --> 36:12.024
Now, your husband, what was his rank
in the military at the time?

36:12.025 --> 36:14.504
I believe he was
a major at that point.

36:14.505 --> 36:16.264
I'm not sure if he was promoted.

36:16.265 --> 36:20.384
He never went up to any
of the authorities and said,

36:20.385 --> 36:23.224
"We're concerned that
this is a crime scene", did he?

36:23.225 --> 36:26.064
No, because he was
very concerned about it and

36:26.065 --> 36:28.064
he was waiting to see
what they would say.

36:28.065 --> 36:30.264
His example to me was,

36:30.265 --> 36:37.224
if I was flying a plane
and someone reported a fire on it,

36:37.225 --> 36:39.464
would you trust me to
put out the fire?

36:39.465 --> 36:42.263
Would you trust my expertise
to put out the fire?

36:42.264 --> 36:44.743
And he trusted
their expertise that day.

36:44.744 --> 36:47.743
OK, well, ma'am, if you were
on a plane and there was fire

36:47.744 --> 36:50.463
and it continued to burn and
continued to burn and nobody

36:50.464 --> 36:53.983
did anything, at some point you
would say something, wouldn't you?

36:53.984 --> 36:57.103
I would be waiting for a day
that I could put the fire out

36:57.104 --> 37:00.343
and I guess that's why I'm here
today, to help put the fire out.

37:00.344 --> 37:03.543
And this is 18 years later. Yes.

37:03.544 --> 37:07.183
They have telephones in Germany,
don't they? Yes, they do.

37:07.184 --> 37:10.543
And you could have called
somebody the next day.

37:10.544 --> 37:13.503
It's a scary thing to go
to the police and say,

37:13.504 --> 37:16.023
"I think that
there's foul play here."

37:16.024 --> 37:21.223
In fact, during all of 1985,
you didn't call anybody. No.

37:21.224 --> 37:23.904
No, we've had to live with this
all these years.

37:25.464 --> 37:30.103
The first time you actually ever
gave a statement about these events

37:30.104 --> 37:35.463
to anybody in authority was
in the year 2002. That's correct.

37:35.464 --> 37:40.863
And you actually wrote out
a statement to... Detective Holland?

37:40.864 --> 37:42.063
Uh, yes.

37:42.064 --> 37:45.423
OK, and this statement contained
all the significant memories

37:45.424 --> 37:49.863
you had about how Elizabeth Ratliff
died and Michael Peterson's

37:49.864 --> 37:51.503
involvement in that. Correct?

37:51.504 --> 37:54.783
It contained every significant thing
that I could remember at that time

37:54.784 --> 37:57.103
until I began to
remember more things.

37:57.104 --> 37:59.663
OK, well, let's go through
what you could remember

37:59.664 --> 38:01.623
when you wrote to Detective Holland.

38:01.624 --> 38:05.983
Nowhere in this statement
did you say that Michael Peterson

38:05.984 --> 38:09.023
said anything about
there being a cerebral haemorrhage

38:09.024 --> 38:12.423
before the German police arrived.
Did you? No.

38:12.424 --> 38:15.183
In fact, although you knew
this statement was about

38:15.184 --> 38:18.383
Michael Peterson, an investigation
of Michael Peterson,

38:18.384 --> 38:21.983
you didn't say anything about him
at all, did you? No.

38:21.984 --> 38:25.303
Didn't even mention his name.
No, I didn't.

38:25.304 --> 38:28.783
Didn't mention this bloody
footprint you now recall.

38:28.784 --> 38:30.023
No.

38:30.024 --> 38:34.463
You talk about the fact that
Miss O'Hara, now Miss Malagnino,

38:34.464 --> 38:37.783
summoned you.
She was frantic at that point?

38:37.784 --> 38:39.663
She was upset. "Come quick."

38:39.664 --> 38:42.783
By the way, the girls, it says here
the two girls were still in bed?

38:42.784 --> 38:44.583
Yes. That's Margaret and Martha.

38:44.584 --> 38:46.703
They didn't stay there
the whole time?

38:46.704 --> 38:48.183
No, Barbara had removed them.

38:48.184 --> 38:50.983
I didn't remember that until later
when I saw the footprint.

38:50.984 --> 38:53.743
When I remembered seeing
the bloody footprint on the stairs,

38:53.744 --> 38:56.862
then I remembered that she had gone
upstairs and taken them away.

38:56.863 --> 38:58.982
That was one of my flashbacks. So...

38:58.983 --> 39:01.263
Flashbacks?
Have you been having flashbacks?

39:02.303 --> 39:05.702
Flashbacks of the scenes
in short pictures.

39:05.703 --> 39:09.822
Flashbacks come as short memories,
very short memories.

39:09.823 --> 39:13.862
You arrived in Durham
a week or so ago?

39:13.863 --> 39:16.302
Almost two weeks ago. OK.

39:16.303 --> 39:20.462
And you've been in contact
with other witnesses?

39:20.463 --> 39:23.182
I've seen other witnesses,
that's correct.

39:23.183 --> 39:28.022
And just seeing people has
caused you to have flashbacks

39:28.023 --> 39:32.382
of new memories that
you didn't have in March of 2002?

39:32.383 --> 39:36.142
Hearing their voices
has brought back some memories.

39:36.143 --> 39:39.062
The messages,
the images are very, very vivid.

39:39.063 --> 39:40.662
Some of them are in colour.

39:40.663 --> 39:44.302
The things you've been testifying
today that you didn't write

39:44.303 --> 39:48.302
in March of 2002 are the result
of these flashbacks, correct?

39:48.303 --> 39:52.462
A lot of memories came
before I even arrived here.

39:52.463 --> 39:54.182
And those were also flashbacks?

39:54.183 --> 39:55.223
Yes.

39:56.383 --> 39:58.862
I don't know if this is...

39:58.863 --> 40:04.382
I don't know if this is ours or
your mother's. Porcelain de Paris.

40:04.383 --> 40:06.662
I don't know. I mean, it's been...

40:06.663 --> 40:07.862
I have no idea.

40:07.863 --> 40:10.862
Can I take one of
the pie plates to school?

40:10.863 --> 40:13.663
Yeah. We own about ten of them.

40:16.423 --> 40:19.622
I like the blue one better. Yeah, I
don't think this was your mother's.

40:19.623 --> 40:22.542
That's too ugly to be your mother's.
I don't think that one is hers.

40:22.543 --> 40:24.782
I believe...
Yeah, this is your mother's.

40:24.783 --> 40:27.583
Because there used to be
a Rosenthal outlet...

40:30.543 --> 40:33.022
..not far from where we lived.

40:33.023 --> 40:35.942
And your mother would go and buy
an odd piece, you know,

40:35.943 --> 40:39.222
seconds or every now and then
a piece of Rosenthal. This was one.

40:39.223 --> 40:41.502
There are a couple of them,
but over the years

40:41.503 --> 40:44.503
around half of them have been broken
or lost or something.

40:46.143 --> 40:49.822
But literally anything... Oh,
this would be hers. Yeah. Anything.

40:49.823 --> 40:51.782
This is a Rosenthal,
I'm sure it's Rosenthal.

40:51.783 --> 40:54.702
Yeah, anything that says
Rosenthal... Is our birth mom's.

40:54.703 --> 40:57.422
Is your mother's, yeah.
I was with her when she bought it.

40:57.423 --> 41:00.502
Sometimes we'd go by a bunch of it,
so if you go through,

41:00.503 --> 41:02.622
if it says Rosenthal, it's...

41:02.623 --> 41:04.342
So we know what not to break.

