I hope I'm not breaking anything.
I'm just joking.

41:07.783 --> 41:10.341
Yeah, one of your favourite things
to do after dinner would be

41:10.342 --> 41:14.341
walk us around the house
and show us everything that
was going to be ours.

41:14.342 --> 41:16.741
I mean, you always did that.
We always knew.

41:16.742 --> 41:19.342
People are just ignorant,
that's all.

41:21.582 --> 41:23.901
Oh, my God. Portia!

41:23.902 --> 41:26.101
Baby, Portia! Where...

41:26.102 --> 41:27.781
Portia, Portia!

41:27.782 --> 41:29.301
Look, baby.

41:29.302 --> 41:33.221
You know how everyone in Germany
is saying that they cleaned up

41:33.222 --> 41:37.061
so much blood and didn't your dad
say there was no blood?

41:37.062 --> 41:38.541
Well, there's a... What?

41:38.542 --> 41:41.821
The CID agent who went,
who came after the scene,

41:41.822 --> 41:44.261
he wrote a report
and it said that...

41:44.262 --> 41:46.021
The only blood was under her head.

41:46.022 --> 41:49.421
Yeah. Just where she was...
had hit her head. And so...

41:49.422 --> 41:50.861
And so are they making that up?

41:50.862 --> 41:53.221
I don't know. It's hard to tell.

41:53.222 --> 41:55.781
I mean, maybe they did.
She was saying...

41:55.782 --> 41:59.261
She had seven lacerations, they
had to clean up blood, right? Yeah.

41:59.262 --> 42:02.661
And she had a bleeding disorder.
Right. Yeah.

42:02.662 --> 42:07.101
Maybe there was more blood than
people want to remember but...

42:07.102 --> 42:09.541
The bottom line is,
I just don't care.

42:09.542 --> 42:13.661
Like, it happened 18 years ago and
our dad had nothing to do with it

42:13.662 --> 42:16.021
and there's nothing
that they've said

42:16.022 --> 42:20.181
that ties Dad to anything negative,
so it just doesn't make any sense.

42:20.182 --> 42:23.581
It's just what you would think.
Yeah. It just pisses me off.

42:23.582 --> 42:25.541
But it still feels like a big deal

42:25.542 --> 42:28.821
because, I mean, saying that
there's that much blood,

42:28.822 --> 42:32.741
it makes it similar to the...
to our stepmom, and so...

42:32.742 --> 42:36.621
Not only our stepmom.
Well, I mean... To Mom.

42:36.622 --> 42:38.941
To Mom, yeah. And...

42:38.942 --> 42:40.222
I don't know.

42:41.462 --> 42:42.782
Oh, my God.

42:43.862 --> 42:50.541
Did you have the occasion to become
involved with the autopsy of

42:50.542 --> 42:53.221
Elizabeth Ratliff?

42:53.222 --> 42:54.661
Yes, I did.

42:54.662 --> 43:00.341
Do you have an opinion as to
her cause of death? Yes, I do.

43:00.342 --> 43:02.261
What is that opinion?

43:02.262 --> 43:04.701
In my opinion the cause
of death of Mrs Ratliff

43:04.702 --> 43:06.182
was blunt trauma of the head.

43:07.822 --> 43:12.541
Do you also have an opinion as to
the manner of Mrs Ratliff's death?

43:12.542 --> 43:14.461
In my opinion... Objection.

43:14.462 --> 43:15.901
Overruled. In my opinion,

43:15.902 --> 43:19.262
the manner of death in
Mrs Ratliff's case was homicide.

43:21.062 --> 43:25.141
When I think about Elizabeth
Ratliff's death, the question

43:25.142 --> 43:28.741
that strikes me as the most
important one is, when did she die?

43:29.981 --> 43:32.340
And no-one has really
addressed that.

43:32.341 --> 43:36.181
Deborah Radisch apparently hasn't
even thought about that issue.

43:37.381 --> 43:40.820
But if she died at 11pm at night,

43:40.821 --> 43:43.700
which is what the state
would have you believe,

43:43.701 --> 43:49.020
we know as a matter of science that
by eight o'clock the next morning

43:49.021 --> 43:50.780
when her body was found,

43:50.781 --> 43:54.020
it would have substantial signs
of rigor mortis.

43:54.021 --> 43:57.340
It would be stiff,
and people don't forget that.

43:57.341 --> 44:00.980
When you move a body that's stiff,
you remember that.

44:00.981 --> 44:04.180
You can't do a spinal tap
very easily

44:04.181 --> 44:06.740
on a body that's in
full rigor mortis,

44:06.741 --> 44:09.420
or even substantial rigor mortis,

44:09.421 --> 44:12.420
so we know that
she wasn't in rigor mortis.

44:12.421 --> 44:17.060
We know that she couldn't have died
at 11 o'clock at night.

44:17.061 --> 44:21.860
Barbara Malagnino told us that her
body was still warm to the touch,

44:21.861 --> 44:26.020
and so, the physical evidence
is much more consistent with

44:26.021 --> 44:29.740
her having died
some time that morning

44:29.741 --> 44:33.420
than when the state said she died,

44:33.421 --> 44:36.140
late in the evening
the night before.

44:36.141 --> 44:41.300
One of the things that forensic
pathologists sometimes do is

44:41.301 --> 44:43.500
to determine a time of death.

44:43.501 --> 44:44.620
Yes.

44:44.621 --> 44:49.860
Rigor mortis, or "rye-gor" mortis,
is something that medical examiners

44:49.861 --> 44:53.220
use to at least get an estimate
of time of death, right?

44:53.221 --> 44:56.580
Yes, generally a rough estimate,
that would be correct.

44:56.581 --> 44:58.580
And rule of thumb is

44:58.581 --> 45:02.420
it develops pretty much
over about a 12-hour period,

45:02.421 --> 45:06.060
give or take some time... Yes.

45:06.061 --> 45:08.420
And it remains, and
when we're talking about rigor,

45:08.421 --> 45:11.300
we're talking about stiffness
to the touch, right? Yes.

45:11.301 --> 45:16.260
If somebody is found on a step
in a particular position

45:16.261 --> 45:20.420
and rigor has started,
you take them off the step,

45:20.421 --> 45:23.500
they're still going to be in
that position. That's correct.

45:23.501 --> 45:29.860
And so for example, if someone died
at 11pm, one would expect

45:29.861 --> 45:35.500
by eight o'clock or nine o'clock
or ten o'clock the next morning,

45:35.501 --> 45:38.660
certainly by 11 o'clock
the next morning,

45:38.661 --> 45:42.739
to see some
significant rigor, right?

45:42.740 --> 45:44.099
Yes.

45:44.100 --> 45:46.459
And do you know whether or not

45:46.460 --> 45:51.139
anyone who was with Elizabeth
Ratliff's body that morning

45:51.140 --> 45:58.419
from 8am till, say, 12 noon when her
body was moved into the next room,

45:58.420 --> 46:02.780
do you know whether anyone reported
any kind of rigor?

46:04.660 --> 46:07.979
No, I don't know if
anyone made that observation.

46:07.980 --> 46:13.859
And you know, do you not,
that Michael Peterson was at home

46:13.860 --> 46:20.459
with his then wife Patty when
Elizabeth Ratliff's body was found?

46:20.460 --> 46:21.700
Are you aware of that?

46:22.900 --> 46:25.419
No, I don't know.

46:25.420 --> 46:27.939
That's all I have.
Thank you, doctor.

46:27.940 --> 46:31.859
The state of North Carolina does not
intend to call additional witnesses

46:31.860 --> 46:34.139
and with that, the state
of North Carolina would

46:34.140 --> 46:35.859
rest its case in chief at this time.

46:35.860 --> 46:39.539
All right, Mr Rudolf. Will there
be evidence for the defendant?

46:39.540 --> 46:40.979
I'm not sure, Your Honour.

46:40.980 --> 46:45.179
We'll make a decision about that
tonight and if there is evidence,

46:45.180 --> 46:48.499
we'll certainly be prepared
to go forward on Monday morning.

46:48.500 --> 46:52.500
We will see you
Monday morning at 9:30.

